column41: Deployed directly under the middle of the bridge in deepest pool. Very low flowing river. Green rope tied to the side of the bridge closest to Liverpool. VERY difficult access - beware of following GPS instructions. Coordinates not plotting in exact spot, see map in images. Need truck to access
column42: River had much higher flow than deployment. Way more water. Murky

column41: Clear trail leading to a homemade bridge. Sensor to the right around bridge.
column42: Water about 1/2 foot deeper than when we deployed. Flowing slightly faster

column42: Water about 2 feet deeper. Only anchor visible

column41: No clear parking space. Parked on opposite side of river to gas station, upstream of bridge where trees end on the left side of chapel hill drive. River left. Small trail/bushwhack down to river. Local woman said in October she's seen salmon come up the river in 30-40 "bunches". ASF has been doing temperature and other experiments on the river and monitoring Atlantic salmon
column42: Water about 1/2 foot deeper than when we deployed. Flowing slightly faster
